## Style guide

- SEC filing register: formal, legalistic, comprehensive. No promotional language.
- Risk factors should be specific to Echoblast's business (GPU supply concentration with NVIDIA, data center lease risks, customer concentration, competition from hyperscalers).
- Financial statements use GAAP presentation. Non-GAAP measures (ARR, adjusted EBITDA) appear in MD&A with reconciliation.
- Boilerplate safe-harbor language for forward-looking statements.
- CEO (Will Coleman) and CFO (Luis Tran) sign SOX 302/906 certifications.
- Miguel Black (General Counsel) oversees filing preparation.
- Reference real peer companies (CoreWeave, Lambda, Nebius) in competition section.

## Output format

Return the filing as clean markdown following the skeleton structure above. Include all sections with substantive content. Financial tables should use markdown tables. Start with the cover page. No JSON wrapping.
